      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following structure represents a tetrahedral alkoxide-ion intermediate formed by addition of a nucleophile to a carboxylic acid derivative. Identify the nucleophile, the leaving group, the starting acid derivative, and the ultimate product (green = Cl).</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaHdYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b2e14eeb695ef04f002c527fa21767b9dbf6f5ef/OChem_21_EC_024.jpg\" alt=\"Ball-and-stick model shows a five-carbon alkoxide chain where ammonia and chlorine are attached to the carbonyl carbon. The fourth and fifth carbons are double-bonded, with a methyl group on the fourth.\">",
